    (author) Herbert A. Simon
    (category) Quote
    (date) 2026-06-07
    (link)
    (rating) 5
    (slug) poverty-of-attention
    (title) "A wealth of information creates a poverty of attention."
    (updated) 2026-06-07
    (description) Herbert Simon's 1971 line — the origin of "the attention economy." Once information becomes abundant, it stops being the scarce resource; the new bottleneck is attention, the finite thing information consumes. So the real skill shifts from finding information to choosing what to ignore.
